lines.text: along the shores of a silent stream
i'm picking up pieces of my life.
finding out i was living my own dream,
beginning once again.
searched for themes
that i never knew before,
it's like roaming a forest in winter,
searching buds buried in snow.
i leart new languages,
new forms to proclaim.
all the will to be so sincere,
not lying to my self again.
roaming trough the forest's trees,
creating a white snow trail
on fallen leaves.
oh, mother moon illuminate my return,
'cause the road i took is so obscure.
sinking and drowning in a sea of fears,
showing compassion to the moan,
already happened in a day long gone,
the silk dilemma is the key
still for me.
one by one the lights fade out,
the fright-night covers all with her cloak.
cannot name the colour of the dark,
i fall into a dream.
from the lands lying at the end of world
are you bringing this dress as a gift?
"it is made with the purest silk"
she smiled at me,
she never wore the dress.
touching the fabric was like
holding nothing in your hand.
roaming trough the forest's trees,
creating a white snow trail
on fallen leaves.
oh, mother moon illuminate my return,
'cause the road i took is so obscure.
sinking and drowning in the sea of fears,
showing compassion to the moan.
already happened in a day long gone,
the silk dilemma is the key.
hold my hand 'till sun sets off,
i'm proud of what i've done.
at least the days i've spent
are so totally unique.
